Expandable The upright expands an extra 2 inches in depth to maximize your packing capacity. Double Spinner Wheels Double spinner wheels allow for durable 360 degree maneuverability wherever your travels take you.

About Rockland Luggage Since its inception in 1998, Rockland by Fox Luggage has been proudly producing quality luggage and bags for the style savvy traveler. Recognized for its graphic and colorful designs, Rockland prides itself on creating products influenced by current trends in design and fashion. Our products turn heads in a crowd and stand out in the baggage carousel, making it easy for quick exits out the airport. Affordable and travel resistant, Rockland bags are an ideal companion for everything from quick trips to the gym to overnight getaways to extended vacations. Our selection includes: luggage sets (4 piece, 3 piece or 2 piece), hard cases, soft cases, carry ons, rolling backpacks, travel duffels, rolling duffels, cosmetic bags, and kids' backpacks. Over the years, a few Rockland products have been featured in film and television. Their colorful designs make them ideal for an eye catching visual element on screen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Has survived 4 plane rides and a relocation
reviews.reviewText: I bought the pink and its surprisingly sturdy for its price. I have done 4 international trips and the wheels are still on. It does get scuffed easy but nothing a little bit of washing can't fix. I bought 2 others- the black and orange which is also sturdy but the yellow cracked under 50lb of weight and the wheel came off. AT HOME!! It didn't even make the stairs. I wonder if the manufacturer is different or if the color has a strengthening element to it. The plastic on the pink and orange is stiffer while the yellow bows and bends easily. I love this enough to have 2 sets of pin and two sets of black and orange. I stuffed them to 70lbs which made them wobbly and the extended handles creak but survived the airports without damage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Worked perfectly.. seemed durable. Went overseas with this luggage..everything was good and hard case was a bonus in my opinion. I flew delta and the smaller one works for carry on well the bigger one was a check in bag (I think they call it) lol. Good and pretty luggage thank you!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great deal and they are so cute. They got a lot of clothes and shoes. Perfect for traveling. But the wheels on the big one seem like they are going to break off when I have a lot of weight in it. Not very sturdy

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The suitcases are light and can expand to hold more. The wheels are awesome! I travel between Taiwan and the United States often and these suitcases make my trips easier. My ex-wife was so impressed she bought her own set. Delighted with my purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Worth the price! Durable!
reviews.reviewText: I move around a lot and I’ve been living out of my suitcase for the last 5-6months and this set has been through it! It’s been to DC, Houston, NY, South Carolina, Japan, Germany, and the Netherlands in the last 6 months. Other reviews have suitcases that the handle breaks off or the wheels break off for other brands but this one is fine. I was worried but this was well worth the $80 I spent! The only thing is one of the zippers inside stopped working but I think that was also user error and I could probably get it fixed. But overall I’m very happy with this set and highly recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My daughter stuffs these full to and from college across the country. Easy to scuff but zippers are secure and sides do not dent, etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I made a big mistake with this suitcase. Not a good quality and my first experience with Hard side luggage. Don't like them. May buy again because my daughter likes them, but only a top name brand.I did not open the suitcase until the night before my daughter was schedule to leave for Florida. I was not myself as I had a stroke recently. There was a big crack around one of the wheels when I opened it to pack my daughter's clothes. I was left with no other choice than to use this suitcase for her trip. It was too big and not sturdy, which made the manuevering a bit difficult especially with the broken wheel.On my return I called Amazon and explained to them what had happened, and they approved the return. I am waiting to see if my refund will be processed.
